io.purush.java.immutable.collections

Class Stack<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.purush.java.immutable.collections.Stack<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Collection<E>, Seque<E>

    public class Stack<E>
extends Object
implements Seque<E>
    A Stack implementation of a Seque. Internally it is a linkedlist of sorts.
    Op complexity:
    1. Insertion - O(1)
    2. Deletion - O(1)
    This implementation is immutable and thereby threadsafe.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Purush Swaminathan

      • pop

        public Seque<E> pop()
        Description copied from interface: Seque
        Creates a fresh instance of Seque without the end element.
        Since Seques are immutable, pop() is unlike traditional Stacks and Queues. It doesn't remove and give you the end element from the current Seque.
        Use peek() to gather the end element.
        Specified by:
        pop in interface Seque<E>
